Fiat Plans to Sell Three-Year, Seven-Year Bonds in Euros

-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n   a n d   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 
2011-07-05T07:27:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-05/fiat-is-planning-to-sell-three-year-seven-year-bonds-denominated-in-euros.html
Fiat SpA (F)  plans to sell three-year and
seven-year bonds in euros, according to two people with
knowledge of the sale.  The three-year bonds may be priced to yield about 6.25
percent and the seven-year bonds may pay about 7.5 percent, the
people said. Citigroup Inc., Mediobanca SpA, Societe Generale
SA, Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc, Banco Santander SA and UBS
AG are managing the sale.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Martin at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net  